---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayoutContent.astro";
---
<BaseLayout>
  <div class="mx-auto w-3/4 pt-32 lg:pt-32">
    <div class="items-center grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
      <div class="flex flex-col justify-center h-full lg:order-last">
        <div>
          <h1
            class="text-2xl md:text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-900"
          >
            Cónoce más sobre IESTEC
          </h1>
          <p class="text-sm mt-2 font-medium text-zinc-500">
            El congreso de CTI más grande de Panamá cada 2 años.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <img
        src="fotos/IMG_9433.jpg"
        alt="#_"
        loading="lazy"
        decoding="async"
        fetchpriority="auto"
        width="570"
        height="480"
        class="object-cover object-center w-full rounded-xl aspect-5/3 lg:col-span-2"
      />
    </div>
    <div
      class="pt-12 mx-auto mt-12 border-t prose text-zinc-500 prose-a:font-semibold prose-a:text-blue-300 hover:prose-a:text-zinc-900 prose-headings:text-zinc-900 prose-blockquote:text-blue-700 prose-code:text-blue-400 prose-strong:text-blue-500 prose-img:rounded-3xl prose-pre:rounded-2xl border-zinc-200"
    >
      <p>
        Building a digital product today means designing for a world in motion. Our
        users are everywhere—on phones, tablets, laptops, and screens we haven’t
        even imagined yet. The challenge isn’t just to make things fit, but to make
        them feel right, no matter where or how they’re experienced.
      </p>
      <h2>Designing for Real Life</h2>
      <p>
        We start by thinking about the real people who use our products. What are
        they trying to do? Where are they? Are they on a crowded train, or at a
        quiet desk? By putting ourselves in their shoes, we design interfaces that
        are clear, forgiving, and easy to use—even when life gets messy.
      </p>
      <h3>Iterate, Test, Repeat</h3>
      <p>
        Our process is hands-on and collaborative. We sketch, prototype, and test on
        actual devices, not just in the browser. Every iteration is a chance to
        learn: what works, what confuses, what delights. We believe the best ideas
        come from real feedback, not just theory.
      </p>
      <blockquote>
        <p>“Great design is invisible. It just works, wherever you are.”</p>
        <small>- Oxbow Team</small>
      </blockquote>
      <div class="border-t p border-zinc-200">
        <h2>Our Philosophy</h2>
        <p>
          For us, responsive design isn’t a checklist—it’s a mindset. We aim to
          create experiences that are flexible, accessible, and genuinely helpful.
          By staying curious and open to change, we keep improving, so our users
          always get the best, no matter what device they choose.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  
  
</BaseLayout>